Police have appealed for witnesses after a pedestrian suffered a broken leg in a crash with a cyclist.The woman, in her 70s, was injured in Front Street, Arnold, Nottinghamshire, between 12:00 BST and 13:00 on 11 June.Nottinghamshire Police said the cyclist remained at the scene until paramedics arrived but did not leave any details.Officers have urged him to come forward and appealed for witnesses or anyone with footage to get in touch.
